Enable CRM Analytics App Push Notifications

Push notifications let users know when their data conditions have been met. For example, push notifications let users know when a number goal was reached or when it dipped below a specified amount.

Available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience. Available with CRM Analytics, which is available for an extra cost in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions. Also available in Developer Edition.

To enable full content for notifications:

Install the latest Connected Apps package for CRM Analytics Mobile.
From Setup, enter Connected Apps in the Quick Find box, then select Manage Connected Apps.
Choose the Connected App you want to edit and select Display full content push notifications.
Click Save.

Push Notifications can appear to CRM Analytics app users as alerts on a mobile device. In-app Notifications are alerts that keep users aware of relevant activity while using the CRM Analytics app. Tracking Screen shows progress toward goals.

Notifications may include minimal content unless full content is enabled in push notifications. For example, an in-app notification might read "‘Quota Remaining’ met conditions: Amount is 265K and is greater than 250K". The equivalent push notification would be "Notification conditions met" but if full content is enabled it would have the same content as the in-app notification.

Notifications can include text about a metric and its current and threshold values.
title: Enable Push Notifications for CRM Analytics
